- Use Radix UI components for interactive elements (Button, Input, Dialog, Select, etc.)
- Apply Tailwind classes directly in JSX - avoid @apply unless creating reusable styles
- When using @apply, only use in @layer components, never @layer base
- Adjust visual styling to match user prompt mood (corporate vs playful)
- Use consistent spacing and typography patterns across components
- Leverage Tailwind's responsive utilities for mobile-friendly designs
- Prefer composition over customization - use Radix primitives with Tailwind styling
- Use semantic color classes: `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-background`, `border-border`
- Implement proper focus states and accessibility with Radix components
- Use Tailwind's design tokens for consistent spacing: `space-y-4`, `gap-6`, `p-4`
- Apply hover and focus states consistently: `hover:bg-muted`, `focus:ring-2`
- Use Tailwind's grid and flexbox utilities for layout: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2`
- Implement loading states with Skeleton components and disabled states
- Use proper contrast ratios and semantic HTML elements
- Apply consistent border radius and shadows: `rounded-lg`, `shadow-sm`

